# .trivyignore — exclude HIGH-severity transitive CVEs that come from
# upstream `@openai/codex@^0.57`'s bundled node_modules. We can't bump
# them directly without forking the codex CLI; the next codex CLI
# release should pick up newer transitives.
#
# Re-audit 2026-08-01 — by then OpenAI should have shipped at least
# one codex CLI release picking up newer transitives. If still stuck:
# investigate whether we can override via npm shrinkwrap or move to
# install via a vendored package.json.
#
# Pinned by `--include-id-in-skip` style — Trivy matches CVE IDs
# verbatim. molecule-ci#38 Phase-2 (option a — per-template ignore).

# cross-spawn 7.0.3 — fixed in 7.0.5 (regular expression DoS)
CVE-2024-21538

# glob 10.4.2 — fixed in 10.5.0 (command injection via filenames)
CVE-2025-64756

# minimatch 9.0.5 — three CVEs, all in the same DoS-via-glob class
CVE-2026-26996
CVE-2026-27903
CVE-2026-27904

# tar 6.2.1 — six CVEs, file-overwrite + symlink/hardlink path traversal class
CVE-2026-23745
CVE-2026-23950
CVE-2026-24842
CVE-2026-26960
CVE-2026-29786
CVE-2026-31802
